{"lemma":"صالِحِي","slug":"صالِحِي","root":"ص.ل.ح","root_slug":"ص-ل-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-ل-ح","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"صالِح","root":"صلح","pos":"N","occurrence_count":74},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","name","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n24724"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%90%D8%AD%D9%90%D9%8A"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"in good condition, sound, whole"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"honest, upright, good, just, virtuous, right"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"pious"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"suitable, fit"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"copious, frequent"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"good, advantage, benefit, interest"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a male given name, Salih"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Salih (a prophet of Islam who prophesied to the people of Thamud)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of صَلَحَ (ṣalaḥa, “to be good, right, proper; to be sound, whole; to suit; etc.”)."},"ipa":["/sˤaː.liħ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n24724","headword_ar":"صَالِحٌ","root":"SlH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (MA, L, Msb, K,) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalaHa","text_ar":"صَلَحَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (MA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaliyHN","text_ar":"صَلِيحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, L, K,) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaluHa","text_ar":"صَلُحَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (MA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiloHN","text_ar":"صِلْحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) applied to a thing, (Msb,) and to a man, (MA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Good, incorrupt, right, just, righteous, virtuous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honest;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; [see 1;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAsidN","text_ar":"فَاسِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] (MA, L, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SulaHaA='u","text_ar":"صُلَحَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[accord. to general analogy of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaliyHN","text_ar":"صَلِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and app. applied only to rational beings, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAliHuwna","text_ar":"صَالِحُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuluwHN","text_ar":"صُلُوحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.; this being said by some to be a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAliHN","text_ar":"صَالِحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and by others, to be originally an inf. n.; like as is said of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uhuwdN","text_ar":"شُهُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (L.) One says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAliHN fiY nafosihi","text_ar":"صَالِحٌ فِى نَفْسِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man good, incorrupt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in himself"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino qawomK SulaHaA='a","text_ar":"مِنْ قَوْمٍ صُلَحَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a people good, incorrupt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa EalaY HaAlapK SaAliHapK","text_ar":"هُوَ عَلَى حَالَةٍ صَالِحَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is in a good, right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proper, state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAliHN","text_ar":"صَالِحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Suitable, fit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meet:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa SaAliHN lilowilaAyapi","text_ar":"هُوَ صَالِحٌ لِلْوِلَايَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is fit for the office of prefect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) ―         -b3-  And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Much, copious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"frequent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTorapN SaAliHapN","text_ar":"مَطْرَةٌ صَالِحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A copious rain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Yaakoob, L, TA.) And hence the saying of IJ,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ubodilati Alt~aA='u","text_ar":"اُبْدِلَتِ التَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina AlwaAwi A_ibodaAlFA SaAliHFA","text_ar":"مِنَ الوَاوِ اـِبْدَالًا صَالِحًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is substituted for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"frequently."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAliHN","text_ar":"صَالِحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [often] omitted in writing [though not in pronunciation] when it is used as a proper name [so that the name is written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SlH","text_ar":"صلح"},{"kind":"text","text":", or more properly"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"S`liHN","text_ar":"صٰلِحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Durrat el-Ghowwás in De Sacy's Anthol. Gram. Ar. p. 66 of the Arabic text.)"}],"source_refs":["MA","L","Msb","K","IAar"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%B5%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AD/","headword_ar":"صالح","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23351#ce01f2","body_html":"<span>الصالح: هو الخالص من كل فساد.</span>"},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_46","lexicon_en":"Dictionary of Arabic Baby Names (2009)","lexicon_ar":"","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23351#090806","body_html":"نبي عربي من قود ثَمود، ومعناه مؤهّل وقائم بما عليه من حقوق الله والعباد."}]}}